				<li id="16698196" class="cmnt-root" data="-14" data-d="1653707171000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><a class="comment-username" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&u=152426" rel="nofollow"  target="_blank" style="color: #;">Rexis102</a></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578991/Vyke's-War-Spear" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">27 May 2022 23:06</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16698196" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">For those of you who like using this weapon, feel free to keep doing so. My general rule of thumb is if someone’s madness buildup proc doesn’t do any damage, it means they technically dodged it, so I don’t punish them for it. I suggest you do the same, otherwise you’d be taking advantage of a bug. Technically using any statuses at all is taking advantage of a bug, but I’m not gonna say don’t use any weapon with status buildup. Just be fair when wielding this weapon, if your opponent goes mad without taking damage, they deserve to not be punished for it. If they take damage, however, it means you proc’d it on a hit and you may punish accordingly.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16698196" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16698196" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">6</span>